....and it has FAAAR more variety of backing tracks.  Not only does it allow you to choose your chords to solo over (instead of pre-packaging them like Jam Tracks), but it allows you to play EACH chord progression that you define in 42 different styles of music!  They have everything from urban styles to classical to jazz, to Latin flavoured, you name it.  To practice my A Dorian, I had to let Jam Tracks choose my chords and style of music!   I downloaded Chordbot LITE (meaning the full version has even MORE features!) and put my own chords in (which I preferred to those offered by Jam Tracks) and can jam and switch the style of music I jam to every 10 minutes.  Count - that's 420 minutes of jam on one chord progression.  Why are people so amazed with Jam Tracks and it's pre-prescribed 5 or 6 total backing tracks?  I don't get it!  It was replaced and BETTERED by a free program!
Thank you! Jeff Mercer  Cleveland Ohio
